Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.25,0:37:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,修道院专门与美国人做交易\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The Abbey dealt exclusively with American customers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.94,0:37:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们卖孩子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}They sold babies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.48,0:37:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只是为了给孩子更好的生活\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}They only try to give them a better life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.39,0:37:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了赚钱\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Try to make money out of him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.08,0:37:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是问题\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's the problem{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.83,0:37:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我今早给科克的圣心收养院打了电话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I got through to the Sacred Heart Adoption Society in Cork this morning{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.78,0:37:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们给我转到爱尔兰收养局\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}they just referred me to the Irish Adoption Board,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.44,0:37:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对方又把我转给圣心收养院\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}who referred me back to the Sacred Heart Adoption Society.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.27,0:37:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟你兜圈子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Sending you round in circles{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.41,0:37:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毫无帮助\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Then it got helpless{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.27,0:37:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但昨晚我和华盛顿的联系人谈了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but I spoke to some contacts from my Washington days last night,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.35,0:37:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在美国可以有途径追踪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}avenues that can be pursued in America{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.15,0:37:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,障碍是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The stumbling block, of course, is{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.02,0:37:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只能替你走到这一步 菲洛梅娜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}that I can only get so far speaking on your behalf Philomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.40,0:37:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你作为他的母亲\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But as you're his mother,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.81,0:37:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们有义务向你提供所有信息\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}they are duty bound to provide you with the information.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.02,0:38:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的意思是让我母亲和你一起去美国\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Are you suggesting my mother goes to America with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.18,0:38:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你愿意的话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}If you wanted to.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.26,0:38:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的编辑同意报销费用\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My editor has agreed for the bill{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.95,0:38:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得如何 和马丁去美国一趟\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}How would you feel about that, going to America?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.19,0:38:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.76,0:38:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你愿意的话我可以随你一起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I could come with you if you like?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.51,0:38:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不不不 你还要工作\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No no no.you've got your work.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.30,0:38:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我更担心的是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm more worried about{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.37,0:38:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁一路上和我这个愚蠢的老太太\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Martin going all that way with a daft old woman like me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.99,0:38:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不认为你愚蠢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't think you're daft{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.99,0:38:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去你的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh go away with you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.03,0:38:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或老\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}or old{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.41,0:38:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我愿意去\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I think I'd like to go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.00,0:38:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道安东尼有没有想过我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I want to know if Anthony ever thought about me,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.60,0:38:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我每天都在思念他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}cos I've thought about him every day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.96,0:38:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,华盛顿 很好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh,Washinton,lovely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.66,0:38:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你自己打的包吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Did you pack your baggage yourself?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.25,0:38:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我女儿帮我的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My daughter helped me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.60,0:38:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这待遇真高级 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm getting royal treatment Martin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.95,0:38:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感觉像教皇一样\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I feel like the Pope{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.81,0:39:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保护你的髋关节\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}well, save your hip{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.18,0:39:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么好看的书吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Have any interesting book?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.56,0:39:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的刚读完\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I've just finishing mine{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.68,0:39:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些枯燥\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}it's a bit dull ,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.11,0:39:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关于十月革命\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}about the October revolution{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.91,0:39:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政治价码\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}it's all just political horse-trading{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.69,0:39:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的也是讲马的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Mine was about horses too.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.92,0:39:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讲一个叫罗伯特的小伙子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It was about this fella Robert{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.18,0:39:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和一个贵妇订了婚\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and he's engaged to this duchess{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.03,0:39:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是医生的儿子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and he's the son of a doctor{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.50,0:39:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常出色\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}so he's done very well for himself{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.86,0:39:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但那个女人很差劲\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but this woman oh she's terrible{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.05,0:39:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很虚荣\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}is vain as she like{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.46,0:39:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总爱照镜子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and always looking herself in the mirror{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.71,0:39:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之类的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}that's sort of thing{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.53,0:39:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她觉得他像一潭死水一样乏味\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And she thinks he's dull as ditch-water{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.71,0:39:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以他开始对马感兴趣\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}so he takes up an interest in the horses{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.43,0:39:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样才能融入上层社会\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}because that way he's getting upper classes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.56,0:39:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来他在马厩遇见了一个姑娘\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and of course he meets the girl down the stables{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.03,0:39:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她出身卑微\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and she's not even a doctor's daughter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.20,0:39:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她父亲是农场工人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}her father's just a farmhand and{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.58,0:39:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他只有一只脚\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}he only has one foot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.43,0:39:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不管怎样他俩相爱了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but anyway of course they fall in love,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.37,0:39:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他现在左右为难\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and he's now torn between{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.18,0:39:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,娶了贵妇 他就能当公爵\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}becoming a duke because when he marries her{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.14,0:39:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为领主之类的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}he'll become lord of the manor and all that sort of thing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.14,0:39:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而他爱的那个马厩姑娘\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and the stable girl who he loves{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.11,0:39:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,名下一个子儿也没有\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but hasn't a penny to her name{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.14,0:39:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了婚礼那天\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}so the big day's coming the wedding{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.83,0:40:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那姑娘 啊 她太可爱了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and this girl, oh she is lovely,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.06,0:40:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她说罗伯特必须尽他的义务\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she says Robert has to do his duty{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.57,0:40:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都已经定好了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and he's already spoken for{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.26,0:40:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他试着礼服\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and he's being measured up for his suit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.35,0:40:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是心不在焉\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but you can tell his heart's not in it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.00,0:40:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他一直想着马和马厩姑娘\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}cos all the while he's thinking about the horses and the stable girl.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.74,0:40:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有人都在教堂等他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}So they're all there waiting for him in the church,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.05,0:40:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,达官贵人们\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}the hoi polloi,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.21,0:40:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但事情是这样的 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but the thing is Martin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.54,0:40:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个贵妇\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}this duchess{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.27,0:40:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只想刁难罗伯特\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she just wants Robert to spite the fella{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.40,0:40:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是她的真正意图\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she's really after{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.54,0:40:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到最后贵妇发现\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}then towards the end the duchess finds out that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.35,0:40:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马厩姑娘想打罗伯特的主意\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}the stable girl has designs on Robert{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.88,0:40:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在那之前 姑娘的瘸腿老爹死了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but before that the father without the foot dies{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.64,0:40:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她爹临死前对罗伯特说\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but before he does he says to Robert{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.49,0:40:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,追随你的内心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}"follow your heart"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.45,0:40:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后贵妇对马厩姑娘下了驱逐令\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and then the duchess gives the stable girl her marching orders{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.21,0:40:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她开始收拾行囊\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and she packs her things{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.54,0:40:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面有辆小马车等着她\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}there's a pony and trap waiting for her outside and{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.35,0:40:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她上了马车\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}when she climbs into it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.56,0:40:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问你知道去哪儿吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she asks do you know where we're going?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.93,0:40:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车夫转过身来\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And the driver turns round{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.40,0:40:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不就是心上人罗伯特吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and if it isn't yer man Robert.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.64,0:40:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And he says{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.10,0:40:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要带你去一个再也不受伤害的地方\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm taking you to a place where no one can hurt you anymore{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.30,0:40:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我根本没想到这个结局 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well, I didn't see that coming Martin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.83,0:40:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一百万年也想不到\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}not in a million years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.38,0:40:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是个不错的惊喜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's nice to have a surprise.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.96,0:40:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听起来很引人入胜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Sounds like a real page turner.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.56,0:40:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以借你看\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You can borrow it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.45,0:40:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,算了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That'ok{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.08,0:40:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我已经看完了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No no.I've just finished it now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.59,0:40:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感觉像是已经看了一遍了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I almost feel like I've read it{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.05,0:41:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,《拖鞋和马蹄铁》\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The Slipper And The Horseshoe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.92,0:41:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 还是一个系列的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh,this is the series of them{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.27,0:41:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香槟还是鸡尾酒\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Champagne or Buck's Fizz?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.68,0:41:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了 谢谢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No,thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.62,0:41:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,免费的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Free{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.14,0:41:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哎呦 给我来杯鸡尾酒\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I say! I'll have a Buck's Fizz!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.69,0:41:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.09,0:41:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真好 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well, that's lovely.Martin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.48,0:41:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我坐过瑞安航空 什么都要花钱\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You have to pay for everything on Ryan Air.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.95,0:41:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不算高级\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well,they don't have top class{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.60,0:41:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿莱克斯 你好吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Alex, how are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.99,0:41:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自从你离开单位 就没见过你\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Not seen you since you left the department.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.53,0:41:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还打算给你打电话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I was gonna call you actually{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.43,0:41:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们还是朋友吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Still friends?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.45,0:41:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes of course.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.38,0:41:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望你别以为是我告的密\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Listen, I hope you didn't think I dropped you in it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.28,0:41:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说实话 不用担心 这是战争迷雾\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Don't worry about it honestly, fog of war.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.41,0:41:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 连带伤害\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yeh, collateral damage.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.38,0:41:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去美国干什么 采访选举\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}So what are you up to? Off to the primaries?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.27,0:41:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 - 不 他帮我找...\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes,yes. - No.He's helping me look...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.79,0:42:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,采访一个情感类的故事\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's a human interest story.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.93,0:42:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝好运 我得赶快回去了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well good luck with it.I'd better scoot back.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.96,0:42:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Ok{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.67,0:42:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思 马丁 我们是不是该装作不认识\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry Martin should we pretend we don't know each other?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.07,0:42:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 他只是我以前的同事\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No,he is just someone I used to work,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.20,0:42:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,政治顾问 我只是想回避他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}a spin doctor,I just try to avoid him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.35,0:42:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那边是头等舱吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Is that First Class in there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.39,0:42:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工作补贴\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's a perk of the job.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.34,0:42:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坐头等舱\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Just because you're in first class{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又不代表他是头等人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}it doesn't make you a first class{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.30,0:42:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还好了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He's all right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.16,0:42:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他去屎吧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I think he needs a good swipe of shite.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.06,0:42:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说的没错\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes.you're probably right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.93,0:43:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 你枕头上也有巧克力吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Martin, did you have a chocolate on your pillow?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.06,0:43:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes.I did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.10,0:43:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球另一边的生活\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}How the other half lives,see?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.32,0:43:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,瞧这景色\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}look at that view.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.09,0:43:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我那边只能看到空调管道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Mine is of the air condition ducts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.83,0:43:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,档案室的卡罗琳打来的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Caroline from the records office.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.05,0:43:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是推测\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well,that's conjecture.guess work.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.69,0:44:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好的推测 把名单发给我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Good guess work.Send over the long list,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.02,0:44:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好极了 明早再和你联系 好的再见\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Great.Fablulous.I'll talk to you in the morning.Okay,bye-bye.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.21,0:44:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出去散步吗 倒一下时差\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Shall we go for a walk, try and shake off our jet lag?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.59,0:44:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说一直想看林肯纪念堂\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You said you wanted to see the Lincoln Memorial?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.88,0:44:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,林肯以后再看\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well, we can go to see Mr. Lincoln.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.45,0:44:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在还是看电视吧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Or, we could watch on my television...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.95,0:44:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝地奶霸\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Big Momma's House{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.09,0:44:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个黑人打扮成胖女人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's about a little black man who pretends to be a fat black lady.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.39,0:44:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以前看过片段\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}They showed some of it on the tv{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.75,0:44:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他被追着满大街跑\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and they're all chasing after him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.53,0:44:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特别滑稽 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}it looked hilarious Martin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.67,0:44:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真不可思议\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Isn't he wonderful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.34,0:44:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直想亲眼看看他坐在那把大椅子上\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I've always wanted to see him in his big chair.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.68,0:44:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的确是个大个子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well he was big man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.86,0:44:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,6.4英尺 最高的美国总统\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Literally.Six foot four. Tallest American president.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.89,0:44:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能看得出 坐着还显得那么高\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I can see that. He's tall even sitting down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.44,0:44:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有个朋友\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I had a friend{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.06,0:45:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她女儿花钱带她去佛罗里达\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and her daughter paid for her to go to Florida{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.09,0:45:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,祝她七十大寿\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}for her seventieth birthday{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.44,0:45:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她跟我说\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and she said{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.10,0:45:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲儿 餐厅食物的分量\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}"Phil, the size of the portions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.51,0:45:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多的你都不敢相信\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}you wouldn't believe".{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.27,0:45:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来给你拍张快照\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm going to take your quick picture.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.46,0:45:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,文章上用的?\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Is this for the article?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.37,0:45:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有点担心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Only I'm a little bit worried you see,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.62,0:45:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果找到他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}because if I find him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.50,0:45:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也许不赞成我把一切告诉记者\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}he might be very disapproving of talking to the papers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.45,0:45:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,家事应该很隐私的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Families are very private things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.28,0:45:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 站在那里\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Alright,go and stand by there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.39,0:45:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说的没错 但追寻他是很大一笔开销\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}that's true, but tracking him down's a very expensive business{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.27,0:45:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以就算是等价交换了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}so it's like a  quid pro quo.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.17,0:45:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What does that mean?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.13,0:45:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是一物换一物\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It means this for that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.67,0:45:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But don't worry{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.50,0:45:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不满意的话我不会发表\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I won't write anything you're unhappy with.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.75,0:45:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是讲述事实\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Just the truth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.59,0:45:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我担心的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's the thing I'm worried about.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.39,0:45:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该面带微笑还是严肃点\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Should I smile or should I be serious?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.10,0:45:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拍一张开心的 一张不开心的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Let's do one happy, one not so happy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.10,0:45:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我好害怕\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm getting scared{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.39,0:45:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越来越近了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}now we're getting closer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.48,0:45:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么多年 不知道安东尼是否遭受不幸\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}All these years, wondering whether Anthony was in trouble,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.63,0:45:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是进监狱\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}or in prison{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天知道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}or goodness knows what.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.50,0:46:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要我一刻没了解真相\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}As long as I didn't know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.48,0:46:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就能一直安慰自己\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I could always tell myself that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.45,0:46:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他正在某个角落过得很幸福 一切安好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}he was happy somewhere, and he was doing all right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.02,0:46:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可要是他死在越战怎么办\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But what if he died in Vietnam?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.91,0:46:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或失去双腿\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Or came back with no legs,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.16,0:46:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是流落街头\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}or lived on the street.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.04,0:46:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别自寻烦恼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Don't upset yourself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.84,0:46:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道的事就是不知道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}We don't know what we don't know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.52,0:46:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,面对事实的时候应对好就行了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}We'll just have to deal with that when we get there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.85,0:46:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要是个瘾君子怎么办 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What if he was a drug addict Martin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.27,0:46:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要有肥胖症怎么办\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}what if he was obese?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.02,0:46:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肥胖症\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Obese?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.88,0:46:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我看过一个纪录片说\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I watched this documentary that said{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.73,0:46:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,许多美国人都是大胖子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}a lot of Americans are huge{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.66,0:46:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,万一他也是怎么办\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}what if that's happened to him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.78,0:46:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么会想到他有肥胖症\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But what on earth makes you think he'd be obese?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.17,0:46:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为食物分量很大\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Because of the size of the portions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.51,0:46:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Hello?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.64,0:46:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我这有浴衣 菲洛梅娜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No,I've got a both robe,Philomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.05,0:46:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 每个房间都有两件\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes,there're two in every room{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有两双拖鞋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And slippers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.57,0:47:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只是有点时差反应\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Ok.You just a little bit jetlag,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.32,0:47:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,躺下休息吧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}just try to get lie down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.40,0:47:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 晚安\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Alright,good night.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.51,0:47:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都好吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}how's everyone?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.51,0:47:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都很好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}We're all good,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.23,0:47:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丹尼赢了橄榄球比赛 还触地得分了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Danny won his rugby match today and he scored a try.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.82,0:47:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真棒\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's fantastic{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.02,0:47:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲洛梅娜怎么样\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}How's Philomena?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.13,0:47:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我终于明白了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well, I finally seen, first hand,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.08,0:47:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读者文摘 每日邮报 和浪漫小说给人影响有多深\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}what a lifetime's diet of Reader's Digest, the Daily Mail and romantic fiction can do to a person's brain.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.21,0:47:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她一直对宾馆员工念叨他们多友好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}She keeps telling all the hotel staff how kind they are.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.09,0:47:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她肯定以为他们是志愿者\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she must think they're volunteers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.35,0:47:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她今天和四个人说 他们每个都是"万里挑一"\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}She tell four people today who were all, "one in a million".{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.05,0:47:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是怎样的概率啊\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What are the chances of that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.40,0:47:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别贫了 她只是个爱尔兰小老太太\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh come on she's just a little old Irish lady.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.81,0:48:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Is something alright?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.83,0:48:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 之前想跟你说 可是忘了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Martin I wanted to tell you something earlier but it slipped my mind,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.63,0:48:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本想打电话的 我又不记得号码\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and I was going to tell you on the phone but I forgot the number,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.71,0:48:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 我想说的是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What I want to say Martin is that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.10,0:48:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你帮我找儿子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Thank you for helping me to look for my son.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.30,0:48:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你丢了工作\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I know you got the sack from your job{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.33,0:48:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是十点新闻 是其他的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}not News At Ten,the other one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.33,0:48:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们的损失就是我的收获\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But that their loss is my gain.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.37,0:48:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.50,0:48:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚安 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Good night Martin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.41,0:48:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚安 菲洛梅娜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Good night.Philomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.33,0:49:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 卡罗琳 我是马丁·西克史密斯\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Hi Caroline it's Martin Sixsmith.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.10,0:49:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想核对一下\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I just wanted to check{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.86,0:49:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,移民资料\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}the file with the immigration cuttings{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.27,0:49:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你核对过了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I know you've checked,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.46,0:49:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给我发个链接好吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but could you send me a link anyway{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.84,0:49:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们英国没有墨西哥人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}we don't really have Mexicans in England,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.33,0:49:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是有印度人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}we have the Indians instead,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.99,0:49:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人人都爱咖喱\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and everybody loves curry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.03,0:49:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 那边有蛋卷\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Martin they've got omelettes over there,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.81,0:49:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,薄饼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}pancakes{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.64,0:49:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有华夫饼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and waffles and{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.08,0:49:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么馅的都有\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}any filling{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.98,0:49:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有麦片粥 培根 香肠\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and cereals and bacon and sausage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.61,0:49:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要什么有什么 -- 我看见了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and anything you want{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.80,0:49:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早餐都包括在房钱里面吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The breakfast is included isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.15,0:49:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 我不饿\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It is.I'm just too early{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.80,0:49:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太早了还没什么胃口\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My stomach hasn't woken up yet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.06,0:49:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Mine wakes up before I do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.34,0:49:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要吃火腿 瑞士奶酪 和麦片粥\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm having a ham and Swiss cheese omelette{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.20,0:49:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给你也带点\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}shall I get you one?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.94,0:50:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了 我还不饿\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No.I'm just not hungry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.70,0:50:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不来点蓝莓\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Why don't you have some blueberries?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.67,0:50:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要咖啡吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Coffee?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.31,0:50:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不了 谢谢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No thanks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.20,0:50:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想自取早餐\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Okay if you want to help yourself to breakfast over there{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.66,0:50:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冷热餐都有\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}we have a hot and cold buffet,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.56,0:50:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新鲜水果 麦片粥 -- 她刚告诉我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}fresh fruit and cereal.-- She just told me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.83,0:50:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,松饼 各种口味的蛋卷\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}muffins, omelettes with a choice of filling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.78,0:50:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早餐有什么我全知道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I know exactly what is available for breakfast.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.26,0:50:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有现烤的薄饼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}We also have fresh pancakes?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.38,0:50:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.89,0:50:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在私人谈话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm trying to have a private conversation here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.46,0:50:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 先生\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My apologies sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.93,0:50:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别那么没礼貌\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}There's no need to be rude.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.39,0:50:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她人很好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}She's a very nice person.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.21,0:50:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 她一定是万里挑一\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes, I'm sure she's one in a million{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.48,0:50:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或千里挑一\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}or one in a hundred thousand.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.16,0:50:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意思\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What do you mean?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.15,0:50:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你至少跟十个人这么说了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You've said that to at least ten people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.82,0:50:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就计算一下\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}so that's just maths.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.93,0:50:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你高高在上时 应该对下面的人都好些\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You should be nice to people on the way up{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.95,0:50:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等你掉下来时 说不定还会遇到他们\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}because you might meet them again on the way down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.75,0:50:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们这些人应该认识到这点\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You of all people would understand that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.43,0:50:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我宁愿你对我更没礼貌\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'd rather you were rude to me{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.64,0:50:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都别那样对他们\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}than the nice people who work here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.03,0:50:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.60,0:50:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是在帮你找儿子\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm trying to help you find your son,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.36,0:50:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我们来的原因\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}that's why we're here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.15,0:50:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安静一下\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}So have some quiet time?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.39,0:51:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你出生在墨西哥\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Were you born in Mexico?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.75,0:51:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来自奇瓦瓦\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm from Chihuahua{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.96,0:51:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定喜欢墨西哥玉米脆片\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You must like nachos?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.81,0:51:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我外孙女娜塔莉让我喜欢上它了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My grand daughter Natalie got me into them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.18,0:51:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没去过墨西哥\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I've never been to Mexico{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.48,0:51:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我相信一定是个好地方\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I believe it's lovely{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.42,0:51:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了拐卖儿童\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}apart from the kidnappings{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.85,0:51:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}安东尼·李 移民资料
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.57,0:51:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}赫斯博士和太太 与两名家庭新成员玛丽和迈克尔\N到达米德韦机场 两个孩子是从爱尔兰领养
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.76,0:52:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}迈克尔·赫斯 出生日期 1952年7月5日
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.18,0:52:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}迈克尔·赫斯 1952年生于爱尔兰\N1955年随养父母到美国
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.36,0:52:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}老布什总统的首席法律顾问\N里根执政时期共和党重要顾问
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.68,0:52:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\1c&H00FFFF&\3c&H000000&}死于1995年8月15日
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.67,0:52:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有蓝莓了 我给你拿了些木莓\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}They've run out of blueberries so I got you raspberries instead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.19,0:52:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起 我忘了要安静\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry. Quiet time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.38,0:53:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我的安东尼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's my Anthony.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.03,0:53:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经死了 是不是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He's dead... isn't he.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.06,0:53:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 对不起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes,I'm sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.31,0:53:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的对不起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm sorry.I'm so sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.48,0:54:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他死了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He's dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.17,0:54:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁死了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Who's dead?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.96,0:54:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个儿子 8年前就死了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The son,he died 8 years ago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.37,0:54:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天哪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh,dear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.92,0:54:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死因是什么\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What did he die of?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.86,0:54:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道 没去查\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't know, I didn't find out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.33,0:54:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我人在机场\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm at the airport{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.06,0:54:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,机场\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}The airport?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.79,0:54:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她想回家 和女儿在一起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she wants to get back, be with her daughter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.20,0:54:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,故事怎么办\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What about the story?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.36,0:54:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经死了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well,he's dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.75,0:54:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死或生 悲剧或喜剧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Dead or alive, happy or sad{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.27,0:54:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都很好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}they're both good.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.76,0:54:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想办法把这个故事写下去\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Spin it, find a story.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.71,0:54:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着 我要是留下 而她回去了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Look,if I stay here and she goes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.54,0:54:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我找谁去问\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}no-one's going to answer my questions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.40,0:54:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就别让她走\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Then keep her there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.81,0:54:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么 她现在很痛苦\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What? Come on,she's in bits.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.00,0:54:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就好像再一次失去了他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's like she's lost him all over again.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.03,0:54:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这句台词很不错 记下来\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's great write that line down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.89,0:55:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可是有合约在身\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}you signed a contract.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.49,0:55:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是认真的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Are you serious?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.61,0:55:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 有新消息再打给我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes.Call me when you've got something.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.27,0:55:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 是我的编辑\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Sorry,my editer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.13,0:55:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来要用那张不开心的照片了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It is suppose to use the not happy photo now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.17,0:55:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes,I suppose so.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.04,0:55:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想起在游乐场那天\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I remember that day at the fair,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.54,0:55:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他父亲装成老头逗我开心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}his father made me laugh by pretending to be an old man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.46,0:55:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也装成老太太逗他开心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And then I made him laugh by pretending to be an old woman.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.95,0:55:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我成老太太了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And now I am one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.10,0:55:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我永远都无法知道安东尼是否想起过我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'll never know if Anthony ever thought about me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.96,0:56:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我永远都没机会说对不起\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'll never be able to say sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.92,0:56:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有一小时就登机了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Start boarding for about one hour.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.33,0:56:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 机票还可以改签吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Tell me Martin.Do we have flexible tickets{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.76,0:56:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 可以\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes,I think so.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.70,0:56:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果计划有变 就能改航班\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You can change another flight if change your plans?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.98,0:56:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.35,0:56:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们也许不该今天走\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Suppose we didn't get on the airplane tonight.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.12,0:56:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直在这等一个征兆\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Because I've sitting here waiting for sign.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.91,0:56:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但什么都没有\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But haven't had one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.15,0:56:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是我决定在这里多待一段时间\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}So I made a decision myself I'd like to stay here longer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.58,0:56:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你打算这么做的话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well,if that's what you want to do{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.35,0:56:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.23,0:56:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想和认识他的人谈谈\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'd like to talk to someone who actually met him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.42,0:56:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那我们留下\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Then we'll stay{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.53,0:57:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我收到了一张安东尼的照片\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I've been sent a picture of Anthony{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.59,0:57:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要看看吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Do you want to see it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.50,0:57:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.13,0:57:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes please.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.92,0:57:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里根总统\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}President Reagan{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.52,0:57:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是明天要和我们见面的女士发来的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It's from a woman we could meet tomorrow{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.55,0:57:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她叫玛茜娅·韦勒\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}called Marcia Weller,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.52,0:57:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她曾经是安东尼的同事\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}she was a colleague of Anthony's{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.03,0:57:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他看上去很聪明\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He looks very smart.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.92,0:57:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喝一杯吗 白兰地\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Now shall we have a drink? Brandy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.89,0:57:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,啊 都没了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh they're all gone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.49,0:57:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马丁 这个人好像你\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Martin.This man looks just like you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.11,0:57:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It is me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.64,0:57:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迈克尔·赫斯\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Michael Hess.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.43,0:57:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我见过他 -- 在哪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I met him. Where?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.00,0:57:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在白宫\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}At the White House.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.09,0:57:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天哪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh dear God.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.51,0:57:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大概十年前 我还在BBC工作\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It was 10years ago when I was with the BBC.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.16,0:57:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他什么样\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What was he like?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.04,0:57:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我记不起了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I can't remember it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.50,0:58:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和党的事情\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It was a Republican thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.61,0:58:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好好想一想\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}You must remember something.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.85,0:58:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们进去时他就在门口\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was by the door as we entered.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.55,0:58:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还和他握了手\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I shook hands with him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.82,0:58:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么握的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What was the handshake did he have?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.01,0:58:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坚定有力\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}It was firm{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.61,0:58:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他握手软弱无力 我一定记得很清楚\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}If I'd have remembered if a weak handshake.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.89,0:58:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可没人会在那个位置上软弱无力地握手\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No-one would get to that position with a weak handshake{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.35,0:58:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他握手有力  还有呢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}So he had a firm handshake?What else?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.07,0:58:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很聪明\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was smart.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.24,0:58:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直希望他聪明\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh I always dressed him smart.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.57,0:58:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能想起他说了什么吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Did you remember anything he said?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.03,0:58:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"你好" 也许可能是"嗨"\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Hello,or might be hi{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.45,0:58:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很彬彬有礼\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was polite.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.44,0:58:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很聪明 握手很有力\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was smart, and he had a firm handshake.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.96,0:58:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还说了"你好"\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He said."Hello"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.12,0:58:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还说了"你好""你好"\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He said."Hello"Hello{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.73,0:58:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还很彬彬有礼  -- 太好了 马丁!\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was polite. -- Oh Martin!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.64,0:58:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认识您儿子有十年了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I knew your son for about ten years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.07,0:58:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是里根和布什政府的高级法律顾问\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He was senior legal counsel to both the Reagan and Bush administrations.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.98,0:58:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干得不错嘛\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Didn't do too badly, did he?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.32,0:59:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要是在我身边 永远也干不了这工作\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He'd never have got a job like that if he'd stayed with me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.98,0:59:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想他会在麦克埃弗利斯上班\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I think he would have worked at McEverleys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.73,0:59:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是卡斯尔巴的一间律师事务所\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}They're a firm of solicitors in Castlebar.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.67,0:59:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他提起过爱尔兰吗 玛茜娅\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Did he ever mention Ireland to you Marcia?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.20,0:59:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't think so{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.31,0:59:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我有他妹妹玛丽的电话\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But I have a number for his sister, Mary,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.69,0:59:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和他一起从爱尔兰来的妹妹\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}who came from Ireland with him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.26,0:59:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以帮你联系她\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I can put you in touch with her?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.18,0:59:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好 非常好\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh,great.That's excellent.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.64,0:59:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他看起来很开心\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He looks very happy here,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.09,0:59:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个小伙子是谁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}who's this fella?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.13,0:59:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是他的朋友 皮特\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's his, er, friend Pete.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.37,0:59:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是他女朋友吧 玛茜娅\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Were you his girlfriend Marcia?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.90,0:59:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.43,0:59:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你是否了解 他是同性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't know if you knew, but he was gay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.33,0:59:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,参加正式场合时我经常陪他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I used accompany him when he went to official functions{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.05,0:59:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为共和党排斥同性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}because being gay was frowned upon in the Republican party.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.11,1:00:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是他非常有魅力\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}But he was very charming and very charismatic.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.41,1:00:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我说说他有小孩吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Tell me did he father any children{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.05,1:00:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲洛梅娜 玛茜娅刚才说了 他是同性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Philomena,Marcia just told us that Anthony was gay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.32,1:00:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直都知道\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Oh, I always knew that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.73,1:00:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想他也许是双性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I just thought he might have been bicurious.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.92,1:00:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以前共事过的很多护士都是同性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}A lot of the nurses I worked with were gay{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.02,1:00:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中有一个叫布兰登 他是双性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}but one of them, called Brendan, told me he was bi-curious.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.38,1:00:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得他不会那么坚决\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I don't think he could make up his mind Marcia.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.66,1:00:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没有孩子 抱歉\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}He didn't have any children. I'm sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.79,1:00:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮特爱他吗\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Did Pete love him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.24,1:00:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 爱他\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes he did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.44,1:00:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道他是同性恋\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}How did you know he was gay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.00,1:00:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个非常敏感的小男孩\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Well, he was a very sensitive little boy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.93,1:00:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么些年我一直在想他也许是\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And as the years rolled on I always wondered if he might be.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.75,1:00:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我第一眼看见他穿粗布工作服的照片时\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Then, when I saw that photograph of him in the dungarees,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.41,1:00:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就认定了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}well there was no doubt in my mind...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.12,1:01:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,皮特 你觉得呢\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Pete,what do you think?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.62,1:01:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得它今天有点心情不好 有点暴躁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I think he is in a bad mood.She's got crabby today.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.08,1:01:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不像你\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Unlike you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.49,1:01:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为何守了这个秘密五十年\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Why did you kept this secret for fifity years?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.92,1:01:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的行为是罪过\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What I've done was a sin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.17,1:01:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以要隐藏起来\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}and I kept it all hidden away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.98,1:01:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我心里想\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And then I thought to myself,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.05,1:01:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把它隐藏起来也是一种罪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}kept it all hidden away was also a sin,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.93,1:01:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我欺骗了别人\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}cos I was lying to everybody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.07,1:01:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着事情发展 我陷入迷思\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}And as it went on I tied myself up in knots.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.68,1:01:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底哪一个更有罪\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}worring which was worse sin of the two,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.99,1:01:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生了这个孩子 还是说谎\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}having the babay,or the lying{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.63,1:01:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到最后我也无法下定论了 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}In the end I couldn't make up my mind Martin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.31,1:01:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想问问你 马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I was gonna asking you Martin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.77,1:02:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你写这篇故事 可不可以不用我的真名\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}If you'd be possible not to use my real name to write the story{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.79,1:02:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫我南希还不错\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I was good to called me Nancy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.23,1:02:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直很喜欢这个名字 南希\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I was always like this name,Nancy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.69,1:02:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我侄女叫南希\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}My niece is called Nancy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.01,1:02:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,噢 别人不会以为是她吧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}oh people might think it's her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.40,1:02:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安怎么样\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}What about Ann?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.60,1:02:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安·波琳 多好听的名字 噢 也有人用了\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Ann Boleyn.It's a lovely name,oh but somebody had that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.03,1:02:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须写你的真名 菲洛梅娜\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm going to have to call you by your real name, Philomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.93,1:02:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是规定\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's the way it works.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.30,1:02:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Mary?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.24,1:02:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.81,1:02:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是马丁\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I'm Martin{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.82,1:02:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位是菲洛梅娜 安东尼的母亲\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}This is Philomena. Anthony's mother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.69,1:02:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迈克尔的母亲\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Michael's mother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.62,1:02:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}Okay{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.91,1:02:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们的母亲\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}That's our mother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.81,1:02:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 养母\N{\fnTimes New Roman\fs13\3c&H000000&}I mean,our adopted mother.{\r}
